cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with skeleton-based action recognition, which involves analyzing spatio-temporal relationships in human movements. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and explores different configurations for improving performance on large-scale datasets (cs.MM).
